This paper discusses the interaction between workers' bounded cognitive rationality and the decisions and performance of a multimedia crowdsourcing system. It involves modeling the workers' task selection behaviors using the cognitive hierarchy theory, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also focuses on multimedia crowdsourcing, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The authors also use game theory (cs.GT) to analyze the requester's optimal rewards and quality requirements for the tasks. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of workers' cognitive level on the system's performance, which could be relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY).
